id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nbe1719505542495.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nbe1719505542495.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nbe1719505542495.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"deo1665702690302\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">operation detach\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"deo1665702690302__operation_detach_400627\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines the component behavior when a contained DSP component instance is detached from the parent DSP.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"deo1665702690302__topic_d118484e1_d118485e1_d118486e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104nbe1719505542495_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"deo1665702690302__codeblock_f5h_sbl_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation detach\n      {<var class=\"keyword varname\">scopeBlock</var>}\n      {<var class=\"keyword varname\">variablesBlock</var>}\n      Your code here ...\n   end</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"deo1665702690302__topic_d84537e1_d84538e1_d84539e1_d84540e1_d84541e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d426308e69\">\n                     \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__d6267e20\">Dynamic Server Pages only.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"deo1665702690302__topic_d84542e1_d84543e1_d84544e1_d84545e1_d84546e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d426308e78\">\n                     \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__p_d118496e1_d118497e1_d118498e1\">The Detach operation can only be defined for a contained DSP component.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__p_d118499e1_d118500e1_d118501e1\">DSPs that are contained in another DSP by means of\n            the <span class=\"keyword\">DspContainer</span> widget are attached to the parent DSP when the\n            component instance name is assigned to the <span class=\"keyword\">DspContainer</span> field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__p_d118502e1_d118503e1_d118504e1\">An attached component can be detached by assigning\n            another DSP instance name or an empty string to the value of a\n               <span class=\"keyword\">DspContainer</span> field. A detached component instance stays in the web\n            browser memory until it is removed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__p_d118505e1_d118506e1_d118507e1\">By defining a Detach operation, you can control what happens after an attached component is detached.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"deo1665702690302__p_d118508e1_d118509e1_d118510e1\">Although you can define scope and variables in an Detach operation, you cannot define parameters.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ism1665702594739.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DspContainer</a><p>The DspContainer logical widget provides a default mapping to the dspContainer physical widget. It enables you to embed multiple dynamic server pages in a single web page.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vrb1707739762002.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Operations</a><p>Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "operation detach Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 operation detach Defines the component behavior when a contained DSP component instance is detached from the parent DSP. Explain this code operation detach { scopeBlock } { variablesBlock } Your code here ... end Copy Use Dynamic Server Pages only. Description The Detach operation can only be defined for a contained DSP component. DSPs that are contained in another DSP by means of the DspContainer widget are attached to the parent DSP when the component instance name is assigned to the DspContainer field. An attached component can be detached by assigning another DSP instance name or an empty string to the value of a DspContainer field. A detached component instance stays in the web browser memory until it is removed. By defining a Detach operation, you can control what happens after an attached component is detached. Although you can define scope and variables in an Detach operation, you cannot define parameters. Related Links DspContainer The DspContainer logical widget provides a default mapping to the dspContainer physical widget. It enables you to embed multiple dynamic server pages in a single web page. Operations Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}